---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';

const lastUpdate = 'May 22, 2026';
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy · Wavy"
  description="How Wavy handles your personal data. Transparency, GDPR, and only what's necessary."
>
  <main class="bg-offwhite pt-32 pb-20 md:pt-40 md:pb-28">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-10">
      <p class="font-sans text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.3em] text-teal mb-4">
        Privacy policy
      </p>
      <h1 class="font-serif text-4xl md:text-5xl font-medium text-teal-dark leading-[1.1] mb-3">
        We treat your data with the same care we treat our brands.
      </h1>
      <p class="font-serif italic text-base text-muted mb-12">
        Last updated: {lastUpdate}
      </p>

      <div class="prose-content space-y-10 text-teal-dark/85">
        <section>
          <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl md:text-3xl font-medium text-teal-dark mb-3">
            Who we are
          </h2>
          <p class="font-sans text-base leading-relaxed">
            Wavy is a digital direction and marketing brand founded by Mariana Antunes,
            based in Mafra and Samora Correia (Portugal). We work with established
            businesses in the Western Zone and Greater Lisbon.
          </p>
          <p class="font-sans text-base leading-relaxed mt-3">
            For any question about this policy or your data, you can reach us at
            <a href="mailto:geral@wavy.pt" class="text-teal hover:text-teal-dark underline">geral@wavy.pt</a>.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl md:text-3xl font-medium text-teal-dark mb-3">
            What data we collect
          </h2>
          <p class="font-sans text-base leading-relaxed mb-3">
            We collect only the minimum necessary to respond to you and improve the site:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-outside ml-6 space-y-2 font-sans text-base leading-relaxed marker:text-teal">
            <li>
              <strong class="font-medium">Contact data</strong> you voluntarily provide
              (e.g. when emailing us or booking a call) — name, email, optional phone,
              and the content of your message.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong class="font-medium">Anonymous usage data</strong> collected by Google
              Analytics (only if you accept cookies) — pages visited, time on site,
              device type, country. This data is aggregated and does not identify you.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong class="font-medium">Technical logs</strong> automatically recorded by
              the server (Vercel) during page loads, such as IP address and browser type,
              used solely for security and diagnostics.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl md:text-3xl font-medium text-teal-dark mb-3">
            Cookies and similar technologies
          </h2>
          <p class="font-sans text-base leading-relaxed mb-3">
            We use cookies to understand how the site is used and improve it. On your first
            visit, we ask if you accept. You can decline — the site keeps working normally.
          </p>
          <p class="font-sans text-base leading-relaxed">
            Cookies used (only after acceptance):
            <strong class="font-medium">Google Analytics 4</strong> (anonymised traffic measurement).
            We don't use advertising cookies and we don't share data for that purpose.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl md:text-3xl font-medium text-teal-dark mb-3">
            Why we use your data
          </h2>
          <ul class="list-disc list-outside ml-6 space-y-2 font-sans text-base leading-relaxed marker:text-teal">
            <li>Respond when you contact us.</li>
            <li>Schedule and prepare conversations/meetings with you.</li>
            <li>Understand site performance (aggregated).</li>
            <li>Comply with legal and tax obligations when applicable.</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="font-sans text-base leading-relaxed mt-3">
            We don't use your data for unauthorised commercial purposes, don't sell it
            to third parties, and don't perform automated profiling that takes decisions
            about you.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl md:text-3xl font-medium text-teal-dark mb-3">
            Who we share with
          </h2>
          <p class="font-sans text-base leading-relaxed mb-3">
            We use third-party services that process data on our behalf, under data
            protection agreements:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-outside ml-6 space-y-2 font-sans text-base leading-relaxed marker:text-teal">
            <li><strong class="font-medium">Vercel</strong> — site hosting (servers in US/EU).</li>
            <li><strong class="font-medium">Google Analytics</strong> — anonymised traffic analysis.</li>
            <li><strong class="font-medium">Email provider</strong> — to receive and reply to your messages.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl md:text-3xl font-medium text-teal-dark mb-3">
            How long we keep it
          </h2>
          <p class="font-sans text-base leading-relaxed">
            Emails and conversations: while the relationship is active, or until you
            request deletion. Analytics data: aggregated, kept for up to 14 months.
            Data required by law (invoicing, contracts): for the legally applicable period.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl md:text-3xl font-medium text-teal-dark mb-3">
            Your rights (GDPR)
          </h2>
          <p class="font-sans text-base leading-relaxed mb-3">
            You have the right to:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-outside ml-6 space-y-2 font-sans text-base leading-relaxed marker:text-teal">
            <li>Access the data we hold about you.</li>
            <li>Correct inaccurate data.</li>
            <li>Request deletion of your data ("right to be forgotten").</li>
            <li>Limit or object to certain processing.</li>
            <li>Request a copy of your data in a portable format.</li>
            <li>Withdraw consent at any time.</li>
            <li>File a complaint with the <strong class="font-medium">CNPD</strong> (Portuguese Data Protection Authority).</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="font-sans text-base leading-relaxed mt-3">
            To exercise any of these rights, write to
            <a href="mailto:geral@wavy.pt" class="text-teal hover:text-teal-dark underline">geral@wavy.pt</a>.
            We respond within 30 days.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl md:text-3xl font-medium text-teal-dark mb-3">
            Changes to this policy
          </h2>
          <p class="font-sans text-base leading-relaxed">
            We may update this policy to reflect changes in our services or legislation.
            The current version is always on this page, with the date of last update at
            the top.
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>
